19:15.237 --> 19:17.321
At least you've got Amanda.

19:17.489 --> 19:18.531
She's cool.

19:20.409 --> 19:23.578
Dude, she wants me to meet her parents.

19:23.745 --> 19:25.163
I don't do parents.

19:30.752 --> 19:33.254
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

19:37.009 --> 19:38.593
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

19:38.760 --> 19:41.762
Mr. Winchester, can I talk to you?

19:46.268 --> 19:49.353
Um, I'll wait for you outside.

19:52.649 --> 19:55.943
Look, if this is about the fight,
I didn't start it.

19:56.153 --> 19:58.863
Oh, no, it's not about the fight, Sam.

20:00.908 --> 20:03.701
You know this assignment
was nonfiction, right?

20:05.370 --> 20:06.954
Yes, Mr. Wyatt.

20:07.164 --> 20:09.957
So you and your family killed a werewolf
last summer, huh?

20:15.214 --> 20:17.757
Why would you write
something like this, Sam?

20:17.925 --> 20:19.091
It doesn't matter.

20:19.259 --> 20:21.385
As soon as my dad gets back,
we're leaving.

20:21.803 --> 20:24.805
-So you can flunk me if you want to.
-I'm not flunking you.

20:24.973 --> 20:26.140
I'm giving you an A.

20:31.772 --> 20:33.105
Aside from the werewolf...

20:33.273 --> 20:35.483
...is that really
how you describe your family?

20:36.443 --> 20:37.485
Yeah.

20:38.612 --> 20:41.155
Well, your brother's quite a character.

20:41.323 --> 20:43.824
And your father, he seems, uh, driven.

20:44.576 --> 20:46.619
Anyway, it's good, Sam. It's really good.

20:46.787 --> 20:49.455
Have you ever thought about
pursuing writing?

20:49.623 --> 20:50.831
I can't.

20:50.999 --> 20:52.959
I have to go into the family business.

20:53.835 --> 20:55.336
Family business?

20:56.171 --> 20:58.339
Yeah, my dad's a--

20:58.799 --> 20:59.840
My dad's a mechanic.

21:00.259 --> 21:02.635
So I have to be a mechanic too.

21:02.803 --> 21:05.680
Do you wanna go
into the family business, Sam?

21:07.641 --> 21:09.350
No one's ever asked me that before.

21:09.977 --> 21:11.018
Well?

21:12.688 --> 21:14.772
More than anything, no.

21:18.318 --> 21:19.860
You know...

21:20.112 --> 21:22.863
...I don't wanna, uh, overstep
my bounds here...

21:25.659 --> 21:28.661
...but you don't have to do anything
you don't wanna do.

21:29.538 --> 21:31.289
Look, I mean, I know what it's like.

21:31.456 --> 21:34.292
I come from a family of surgeons,
and that wasn't me.

21:35.544 --> 21:39.213
So, you know, I traded in the money
and prestige of being a doctor...

21:39.381 --> 21:41.674
...for all the glamour you see around you.

21:43.176 --> 21:44.468
The point is...

21:44.636 --> 21:49.557
...there are maybe three or four big
choices that shape someone's whole life.

21:49.766 --> 21:54.145
And you need to be the one
that makes them, not anyone else.

21:55.897 --> 21:58.274
You seem like a great kid, Sam.

21:58.859 --> 22:01.193
Just live the life you wanna live.

22:16.585 --> 22:19.253
We came back here
so you could talk to the teacher?

22:19.421 --> 22:21.255
He's a good guy.

22:22.007 --> 22:23.090
Well, whatever.

22:23.258 --> 22:26.344
Go have your Robin Williams,
"Oh, captain, my captain" moment.

22:26.511 --> 22:28.262
Just make it quick.

22:29.181 --> 22:30.890
[DOOR CLOSES]

22:32.934 --> 22:34.393
[EXHALES]

22:50.118 --> 22:51.619
[SIGHS]

22:52.954 --> 22:54.455
GIRL:
Excuse me, sir?

22:54.623 --> 22:56.457
Can you tell me how to find room 305?

22:57.042 --> 22:58.626
Sure, um--

22:59.086 --> 23:04.298
Down the hall, take your first right
and it's the third door on the left.

23:08.345 --> 23:09.970
Thanks, Sam.

23:11.973 --> 23:13.224
[GRUNTS]

23:14.226 --> 23:15.893
You got tall, Winchester.

23:17.145 --> 23:19.397
[GROANS]

23:32.119 --> 23:33.160
[GRUNTING]

23:37.332 --> 23:39.667
[SPIRIT THUDS]

23:43.547 --> 23:45.631
[PANTING]

23:46.633 --> 23:48.342
[OBJECTS CLANKING]

23:49.469 --> 23:51.429
Trust me, this will help.

23:52.848 --> 23:54.348
[SIGHS]

23:56.893 --> 23:59.562
That ghost is dead.
I'm gonna rip its lungs out!

24:01.356 --> 24:03.023
You know what I mean.

24:03.859 --> 24:05.067
It knew my name, Dean.

24:05.444 --> 24:07.111
My real name.

24:07.279 --> 24:09.738
We burned Barry's bones.

24:10.031 --> 24:12.366
-What the hell?
-Well, maybe it wasn't Barry.

24:12.534 --> 24:15.369
Maybe we missed something.
We just gotta go back.

24:23.420 --> 24:26.255
No way. How did we not see this before?

24:26.423 --> 24:27.715
-What?
-Check it out.

24:30.177 --> 24:32.678
Martha Dumptruck,
Revenge of the Nerds, Hello Kitty.

24:32.888 --> 24:36.015
-They all rode the same bus.
-Okay, so maybe the bus is haunted.

24:36.183 --> 24:40.019
That would explain why there's no EMF
at the school, but not the attacks.

24:40.187 --> 24:43.481
Ghosts are tied to the places
that they haunt. They can't just bail.

24:47.152 --> 24:48.194
Unless this one can.

24:49.946 --> 24:52.907
There's lore about spirits
possessing people, riding them.

24:53.074 --> 24:56.535
Whenever they leave the body, they're
bungeed back to their usual haunt.

24:56.703 --> 24:59.830
But until then,
the ghosts can go wherever they want.

25:00.415 --> 25:03.584
So a spook just grabs a kid on the bus
and walks right into Truman?

25:04.211 --> 25:05.252
It's possible.

25:05.921 --> 25:08.422
Ghosts getting creative,
well, that's super.

25:12.844 --> 25:13.886
[EMF METER WHINING]

25:14.054 --> 25:15.304
SAM:
Definitely ain't clean.

25:15.764 --> 25:18.057
Here ghosty, ghosty, ghosty.

25:18.225 --> 25:20.935
-Come out, come out, wherever you are.
-I don't get it.

25:21.102 --> 25:24.230
No one ever died on this bus.
It's not like there's a body here.

25:24.439 --> 25:26.649
But a flap of skin, a hair--
Hell, a hangnail--

25:26.816 --> 25:30.152
Something's gotta be tying the ghost
to this place. We gotta find it.

25:30.320 --> 25:31.779
SAM:
Yeah.

25:52.217 --> 25:55.553
Got a new driving permit,
issued two weeks ago.

25:55.720 --> 25:57.137
[CLICKS OFF EMF METER]

25:57.305 --> 25:59.557
-Just before the first attack.
-Yeah.

25:59.724 --> 26:02.184
Name of the bus driver
is Dirk MacGregor Sr.

26:02.561 --> 26:04.853
39 North Central Avenue.

26:05.021 --> 26:06.689
-MacGregor?
-Yeah.

26:07.482 --> 26:08.899
What?

26:09.901 --> 26:11.151
I knew his son.

26:12.737 --> 26:14.989
You knew everybody at this school?

26:17.200 --> 26:19.368
[SCHOOL BELL RINGS]

26:24.374 --> 26:25.874
DIRK:
Gotta watch where you're going.

26:26.042 --> 26:27.585
Leave him alone, Dirk.

26:27.752 --> 26:29.712
You never learn, do you, midget?

26:32.924 --> 26:35.175
Get to the bus, Barry.

26:42.767 --> 26:44.018
[STUDENTS MURMURING]

26:44.185 --> 26:46.395
What's the matter? Scared?

26:47.439 --> 26:50.107
Don't worry, I'll go easy on you this time.

26:51.026 --> 26:53.360
Come on, Losechester,
let's see what you got.

26:53.528 --> 26:55.070
Come on, freak.

26:55.238 --> 26:56.405
Freak.

27:00.285 --> 27:01.869
[GRUNTING]

27:05.248 --> 27:07.124
[STUDENTS GASPING
AND CHATTERING]

27:19.554 --> 27:21.138
[STUDENTS GASP]

27:23.391 --> 27:26.977
You're not tough. You're just a jerk.

27:27.145 --> 27:28.562
Dirk the Jerk.

27:28.730 --> 27:30.898
BOY 1: Hey, Dirk the Jerk.
Yeah, that's pretty good.

27:31.066 --> 27:32.816
STUDENTS:
Yeah, totally. Dirk the Jerk.

27:32.984 --> 27:35.569
BOY 2: Dirk the Jerk.
BOY 3: Dirk the Jerk.

27:35.737 --> 27:38.405
STUDENTS [CHANTING]
Dirk the Jerk, Dirk the Jerk

27:38.573 --> 27:39.823
Dirk the Jerk

27:39.991 --> 27:41.158
Dirk the Jerk

27:41.326 --> 27:42.368
Dirk the Jerk

27:42.577 --> 27:46.372
SENIOR: So you were friends with Dirk?
SAM: Uh, yes, sir, in high school.

27:46.581 --> 27:50.125
SENIOR: I don't recall
Dirk having many friends at Truman.

27:50.293 --> 27:52.252
Sit down.

27:53.672 --> 27:55.756
When did, uh-- When did Dirk pass?

27:55.924 --> 27:56.965
He was 18.

27:57.133 --> 27:58.634
What happened to him?

27:58.802 --> 28:01.887
Well, there was, uh--
First, drinking, then drugs.

28:02.097 --> 28:04.390
And then too many drugs and--

28:06.267 --> 28:08.852
He just slipped through my fingers.

28:10.438 --> 28:12.022
It was my fault.

28:13.274 --> 28:15.192
I should have seen it coming, you know.

28:15.777 --> 28:18.654
Dirk, he, uh-- He had his troubles.

28:18.822 --> 28:20.114
What kind of troubles?

28:21.199 --> 28:23.826
School was never easy for Dirk.

28:23.993 --> 28:26.161
We didn't have much money...

28:26.913 --> 28:31.125
...and, well, you know, kids,
they can be cruel. They picked on him.

28:31.418 --> 28:32.668
They picked on him?

28:34.129 --> 28:35.129
Mm-hm.

28:35.755 --> 28:39.633
They called him poor and dirty and stupid.

28:39.801 --> 28:42.636
They even had a nickname for him.

28:42.971 --> 28:45.139
Dirk the Jerk.

28:46.182 --> 28:48.934
-After what happened to his mother, he--
-His mother?

28:50.061 --> 28:52.688
Yeah, Jane, my wife.

28:52.856 --> 28:55.482
She died when Dirk was 13.

28:55.650 --> 28:56.692
Cancer.

28:57.819 --> 29:01.739
I was working three jobs,
so it fell to Dirk to take care of her.

29:01.906 --> 29:03.991
And he was a great kid.

29:04.159 --> 29:09.079
He made sure Jane got her medicine.
He helped her, cleaned up after her.

29:09.456 --> 29:12.750
But, you know,
you watch somebody die, slow.

29:13.585 --> 29:16.086
Waste away to nothing.

29:16.671 --> 29:18.547
It does things to a person.

29:20.592 --> 29:22.301
Horrible things.

29:23.344 --> 29:24.845
I didn't know about his mother.

29:26.055 --> 29:28.599
He-- He wouldn't talk about her...

29:28.767 --> 29:30.017
...not even to me.

29:33.563 --> 29:35.814
Lot of anger in that boy.

29:37.984 --> 29:39.193
I'm sorry.

29:41.362 --> 29:45.365
We'd really like to pay our respects,
Mr. MacGregor.

29:45.533 --> 29:48.786
Um, do you mind telling us
where Dirk is buried?

29:48.953 --> 29:51.497
Oh, he wasn't. I had him cremated.

29:53.750 --> 29:54.792
All of him?

30:00.715 --> 30:02.341
Well, I kept a lock of his hair.

30:03.051 --> 30:06.053
Oh, that's-- That's nice.

30:06.221 --> 30:08.222
Where do you keep that?

30:10.683 --> 30:12.810
On my bus, in my Bible.

30:35.208 --> 30:36.917
Thanks for subbing tonight, Eddie.

30:37.377 --> 30:39.795
My pleasure, coach.

30:53.768 --> 30:56.061
Eddie, you wanna ease up
on the pedal there?

30:57.146 --> 30:59.398
I got it all under control.

31:03.278 --> 31:04.486
[TIRES BURST]

31:04.654 --> 31:05.863
What the hell was that?

31:06.030 --> 31:07.114
[TIRES SQUEAL]

31:13.663 --> 31:14.830
Everyone okay?

31:36.352 --> 31:37.936
SAM:
Dirk.

31:38.646 --> 31:39.813
[GUN CLICKS]

31:41.316 --> 31:42.482
Winchester.

31:43.151 --> 31:45.193
What are you gonna do, shoot me?

31:45.528 --> 31:47.362
Don't need to.

31:48.489 --> 31:52.492
That rope is soaked in salt water, Dirk.
You're not going anywhere.

31:55.455 --> 31:57.581
Everybody stay where you are.
You'll be okay.

31:57.749 --> 31:59.708
Aren't you the P.E. teacher?

32:00.585 --> 32:02.836
Not really. I'm like 21 Jump Street.

32:03.046 --> 32:05.088
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

32:05.256 --> 32:07.966
The bus driver sells pot.

32:08.343 --> 32:10.010
Yeah.

32:17.060 --> 32:18.101
It's not here!

32:19.228 --> 32:22.773
-Where is it?
-No way you'll ever find it.

32:25.193 --> 32:26.234
SAM:
Where is it?

32:26.569 --> 32:30.280
Sam Winchester, still a bully.

32:30.490 --> 32:33.116
You, you jocks.

32:33.576 --> 32:38.538
You popular kids, you always thought
you were better than everybody else.

32:39.207 --> 32:41.917
And to you,
I was just Dirk the Jerk, right?

32:42.085 --> 32:45.796
Now you evil sons of bitches
are gonna get what's coming to you.

32:46.005 --> 32:47.547
I'm not evil, Dirk.

32:51.719 --> 32:52.719
I'm not.

32:53.429 --> 32:54.763
And neither were you.

32:55.223 --> 32:56.556
Trust me.

32:56.724 --> 32:58.725
I've seen real evil.

32:59.394 --> 33:03.397
We were scared and miserable
and we took it out on each other.

33:03.815 --> 33:05.399
Us and everybody else.

33:05.566 --> 33:07.567
That's high school.

33:08.736 --> 33:11.321
But you suffer through that...

33:11.531 --> 33:12.572
...and it gets better.

33:14.242 --> 33:17.119
I'm just sorry you didn't get a chance
to see that.

33:18.162 --> 33:19.955
You or Barry.

33:20.289 --> 33:22.833
Nothing is gonna get better for me.

33:24.085 --> 33:25.627
Not ever.

33:28.256 --> 33:30.090
[EDDIE GRUNTING]

33:31.843 --> 33:33.677
[GROANS]

33:37.765 --> 33:39.433
[STUDENTS CHATTERING]

33:46.441 --> 33:47.607
[GROANS]

33:47.775 --> 33:48.942
[GRUNTING]

33:52.280 --> 33:53.780
SAM:
Dirk, no.

33:55.283 --> 33:57.117
Dean, find the hair.

34:00.079 --> 34:03.206
[SAM GRUNTING]

34:12.967 --> 34:14.967
Hey, buddy, this isn't what it looks like.

34:22.893 --> 34:25.645
[BLOWS LANDING]

34:32.110 --> 34:33.652
[SCREAMS]

34:42.413 --> 34:43.496
[GRUNTS]

34:43.664 --> 34:46.166
[SAM STRUGGLING AND GASPING]

34:47.710 --> 34:49.168
Little help.

34:51.005 --> 34:52.380
Unh.

34:52.547 --> 34:53.632
[CHOKES]

34:54.675 --> 34:57.177
He's giving you the full cowgirl.

34:57.345 --> 34:58.929
Yeah.

35:13.694 --> 35:14.820
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

35:15.446 --> 35:17.864
Five more minutes, Jerry.

35:19.117 --> 35:21.076
[DOOR OPENS]

35:22.161 --> 35:23.203
Amanda, hey.

35:25.164 --> 35:28.375
Uh, Gettysburg Address, 1863, right?

35:33.840 --> 35:34.881
[SIGHS]

35:35.049 --> 35:37.300
History test next period, we're studying.

35:39.178 --> 35:42.806
Come on, baby,
she means nothing to me. Don't be mad.

35:43.724 --> 35:45.892
I'm not mad, Dean.

35:46.102 --> 35:51.648
I thought maybe, underneath your whole
I-could-give-a-crap-bad-boy thing...

35:51.816 --> 35:54.359
...that there was something
more going on.

35:54.527 --> 35:57.696
I mean, like, the way you are
with your brother.

35:59.198 --> 36:00.240
But I was wrong.

36:01.325 --> 36:06.413
You spend so much time trying
to convince people that you're cool...

36:06.622 --> 36:08.331
...but it's just an act.

36:08.541 --> 36:14.546
We both know that you're just a sad,
lonely little kid.

36:14.714 --> 36:16.256
And I feel sorry for you, Dean.

36:18.426 --> 36:20.844
You feel sorry for me, huh?

36:21.179 --> 36:22.929
Don't feel sorry for me.

36:23.097 --> 36:25.765
You don't know anything about me.

36:25.933 --> 36:27.058
I save lives.

36:27.226 --> 36:28.852
I'm a hero.

36:29.020 --> 36:30.270
A hero.

36:33.065 --> 36:34.649
What?

36:38.446 --> 36:40.071
What?

36:41.240 --> 36:43.158
GIRL 1: Good job.
BOY 1: Hey, way to go, Sam.

36:43.326 --> 36:45.160
BOY 2:
Good job, buddy.

36:47.371 --> 36:50.373
BOY 3:
Yeah, nice job, Winchester. Winchester.

36:50.541 --> 36:54.211
BOY 4: Sam, great job
with Dirk the Jerk, ha, ha.

37:01.302 --> 37:02.886
BOY 5:
Nice, Sam. Yeah, you know it.

37:03.054 --> 37:04.971
BOY 6:
Sam the man.

37:05.473 --> 37:08.725
GIRL 2: Hey, Sam, good job, man.
GIRL 3: Good job, Sam.

37:08.893 --> 37:10.810
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

37:12.605 --> 37:14.147
Dad?

37:15.107 --> 37:16.441
Finally.

37:19.278 --> 37:22.739
I can't wait to get the hell out of here.
This place sucks.

37:24.116 --> 37:25.242
[CAR HONKING]

37:33.834 --> 37:36.002
Come on, Sam.

38:02.863 --> 38:05.115
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

38:13.165 --> 38:14.958
Mr. Wyatt?

38:15.376 --> 38:16.376
Yes.

38:18.629 --> 38:20.880
You probably don't remember me, um--

38:21.299 --> 38:25.385
But my name is Sam Winchester,
and, uh...

38:25.553 --> 38:27.804
...I just wanted to thank you.

38:27.972 --> 38:30.265
-For?
-I was a student here.

38:30.433 --> 38:33.893
And, uh, you gave me some advice once.

38:35.229 --> 38:39.566
Winchester. Right, right. Yeah, you, uh--

38:39.775 --> 38:43.028
-You wrote that horror story.
-Yeah, yeah, I did.

38:43.863 --> 38:47.073
Yeah, it's kind of all been
one long horror story, unh.

38:47.658 --> 38:50.410
-What do you mean?
-Nothing, sorry.

38:51.537 --> 38:52.912
So, what was this advice?

38:53.080 --> 38:55.415
I might need to plagiarize myself
down the line.

38:55.583 --> 38:58.126
You told me I didn't have to go
into the family business.

38:58.294 --> 39:00.003
You said I should make my own choices.

39:00.171 --> 39:02.672
Ah, so you managed
to do your own thing, huh?

39:04.216 --> 39:06.426
Yeah, uh, for a while, yeah.

39:06.594 --> 39:10.305
And I think I went to college
because of you.

39:12.099 --> 39:15.435
But, you know, people grow up.

39:16.062 --> 39:17.270
Yeah.

39:18.064 --> 39:20.398
Responsibilities and--

39:23.694 --> 39:25.445
But still, um...

39:26.072 --> 39:28.948
...you took an interest in me
when no one else did.

39:29.909 --> 39:33.244
That matters. So thank you.

39:35.915 --> 39:38.583
Well, you know, the only thing
that really matters is, uh...

39:38.751 --> 39:39.918
...that you're happy.

39:42.129 --> 39:43.380
Are you happy, Sam?

40:26.006 --> 40:28.007
[ENGLISH SDH]

